<body>

<header>
  <h1>Certified MONSTER Gamification Action Plan</h1>
  <p>Your roadmap to building an exciting and transparent gamification campaign!</p>
</header>

<section>
  <h2>1. Finalize Your Branding and Visual Assets</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Confirm the team colors and logos: Black and White, Red and Yellow, Blue and Green, Pink and Purple.</li>
    <li>Final mockups for hats and other merchandise.</li>
    <li>Prepare promotional content for social media, email campaigns, and landing pages.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>2. Set Up Your E-Commerce Platform</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Create Shopify store and set up your branded storefront.</li>
    <li>Upload product listings (hats and other merchandise) with team options and detailed descriptions.</li>
    <li>Set up payment gateway (e.g., Shopify Payments or PayPal).</li>
    <li>Create landing pages for each team (Black and White, Red and Yellow, Blue and Green, Pink and Purple).</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>3. Create a Clear Ambassador Application Process</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Set up an application form for ambassadors (Google Forms or Shopify form).</li>
    <li>Develop guidelines for ambassadors and their tasks (e.g., promoting products, tracking sales).</li>
    <li>Define reward structures (e.g., 50% of profits for winning team, exclusive merch).</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>4. Prepare for Gamification Rollout</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Create a leaderboard system to track sales and ambassador points.</li>
    <li>Ensure first round products (hats) are ready for promotion.</li>
    <li>Start tracking ambassador sales and generate competition hype.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>5. Marketing and Social Media Promotion</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Announce campaign via social media and email campaigns.</li>
    <li>Prepare Instagram and Facebook posts about the gamified team competition.</li>
    <li>Engage followers with interactive posts, countdowns, and sneak peeks.</li>
    <li>Reach out to influencers for collaboration and promotion.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>6. Logistics and Fulfillment</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Confirm your print-on-demand (POD) partner is set up (e.g., Printify).</li>
    <li>Set up shipping preferences and finalize shipping costs.</li>
    <li>Prepare for customer service inquiries (returns, exchanges, etc.).</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>7. Monitoring and Analytics</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Set up Google Analytics to track website traffic and sales data.</li>
    <li>Monitor sales performance and engagement metrics.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>8. Adjust for Continuous Improvement</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Evaluate the effectiveness of the gamification campaign after 1-2 weeks.</li>
    <li>Adapt your strategy based on feedback and data.</li>
    <li>Plan for future rounds of the gamification with new products or team challenges.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="cta">
  <p>Ready to launch your Certified MONSTER gamification campaign?</p>
  <a href="#">Start Now</a>
</section>

